LAB NOC 08 — Cisco 888 Router Baseline Configuration

🚀 Summary  
Real hardware lab focused on applying a complete baseline configuration on a Cisco 888 router after factory reset.

🧩 Problem  
A router in factory state required initial configuration to be integrated into a NOC environment, including identity, security, and operational settings.

⚙️ Solution  
Configured hostname, disabled DNS lookup, applied secure access (enable secret, console login), added MOTD banner, and saved configuration to NVRAM.

🔍 NOC Analysis  
Access method: Serial console (PuTTY)  
Commands used: configure terminal, hostname, no ip domain-lookup, enable secret, line console 0, write memory  
Verification: show running-config, show ip interface brief, show version  
Result: Baseline configuration successfully applied  

✅ Result  
Router configured with full baseline: hostname R1, secure access, MOTD banner, and persistent configuration. Device ready for production use. Ticket NOC-008 closed.

🌍 Real World  
Baseline configuration is the first mandatory step when deploying network devices in production environments, ensuring security, identification, and operational readiness.

